Our DNS isn't properly configured, so in order to hit the database server, you MUST use the FQDN. I noticed in the logs it kept complaining it couldn't connect to the database on my server (with no domain). I added an entry in my /etc/hosts to resolve the hostname (not FQDN) to the proper IP address and bingo!

Your plugin engine (among other things) isn't looking for the FQDN of the database server, just the hostname. Please include this as a note in the oracle configuration guide.

